<Name>Ricardo Gomez<//Name><Rating>4</Rating><Text>This review is more like a 4.5 star review. The service and food here is exceptional. Usually when I come here it's to pickup large orders for friends at work. The girls do a great job of not only getting everyones orders correct, but they do a great job of packaging it, and dividing it into different orders so that I can pay for them individually. For someone who is on the clock picking up for 5+, it makes things so much easier.

Recently I bought their "box lunch" special which came with a small grinder (ham, turkey, or roast beef), one bag of potato chip, and a choice of macaroni, potato, or fruit salad. I believe the meal was between $5-$8 w/o the drink. They have a variety of grinders and build your own or specialty sandwiches. I heard the P.W.D. special is pretty good. It's crispy pastrami, egg salad, cheese, lettuce, tomato & sprouts. Don't forget to add the avocado! They have over 8 meats to choose from, along with 8 different cheeses, including muenster and hot pepper.

The reason I didn't give it the full five stars is because I'm comparing to other sandwich shops I've been too. The quality of food here is still good, and If I had to judge this place by itself my review would probably be a 5 star. Great work ladies!< /Text></record></dataset><record>

<review>Nice trail in the City of Murrieta‚Äôs Cole Canyon Natural Park. This park and trail burned in the 2019 Tenaja fire, and there remains significant fire and erosion damage to the area. Limited parking at trailhead, which is in a residential cul-de-sac. Trails are established yet unmarked. Suitable for hiking, trail-running, mountain biking, and equestrian. Dog & kid-friendly. There are some nice areas near the stream to relax on some giant rocks in the shade of some of the remaining oaks. Good spot to get a local nature fix!< /review><Rate>3< /Rate><user_name>Michelle Markel</user_name>< Date>

<time>1620447783152<//time><Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
Well, it‚Äôs been a couple of weeks since I picked up the 2015 ZX14R Anniversary Edition from AK Motorcycles down in El Cajon, and I couldn‚Äôt be more pleased. Adi went above and beyond the call of duty to facilitate the sale and everything was good to go when I arrived after a long drive from Paso Robles. After a quick once over, I hopped on the bike and rode it 180 miles to Camarillo on a chilly day. Right away I noticed the improvements over my 2007 ZX1400, but the smoothness and insane acceleration were still very apparent.

One of the weird things about the trip was the ride down the Conejo Grade. I was raised in Camarillo and lived there when there was just one stop light and not much else. To encounter bumper to bumper traffic from Thousand Oaks to Camarillo was a shock to the system. Good thing I was on a bike. Even with a bike as large as the ZX14R, splitting lanes was a breeze and easy to do safely, though I can‚Äôt say the same for the other riders who passed me and who were splitting lanes with abandon and way too fast.

After spending the night in Camarillo, and getting the kinks out of my 67 year old body, I hopped on the bike on another chilly morning and rode another 160 miles to Paso without a hitch. Since then, I lowered the pegs 1 1/2‚Äô‚Äô and raised the bars 1 1/2‚Äô‚Äô which makes it far more comfortable to ride for extended periods. I know what some must be thinking about the sacrilege of lowering pegs and raising the bars on a bike like the ZX14R, but trust me, after owning over 20 bikes and having close to 2 million miles on motorcycles, combined with abusing my body with rodeo, jumping out of airplanes,  ranching, racing motorcycles, and other such nonsense when I was young and foolish, you learn to adapt.

Again, Adi and the others at AK Motorcycles made the entire transaction a painless experience and the bike continues to perform flawlessly. Be well and keep the rubber side down. Chris Knudson
Paso Robles, CA<//Text>

<rate>5< /rate><Text>The first time I met Adi was in October 2014 when I was looking to buy my first motorcycle. He sold me a very clean 2008 SV 650S -- almost a year has gone by with this bike and I still have no complaints. Adi is truly a no-pressure salesman, he is very friendly and he provides you a very personalized buying/service experience. For example, right after I bought my bike from Adi -- he proactively compiled and sent me links to a bunch of forums related to riding -- even though I had done the safety course, but as a first time motorcycle owner/rider, those forums did come handy -- and it made me feel like I have become a part of the riders' family. Adi is very honest and straight forward person -- these traits are rarely found in car/motorcycle businessmen. In the service department, I had to take my bike for some minor inspections, for example chain tension didn't seem right, or the clutch seemed too tight. Adi happily inspected my bike, at no cost.  Even to this day, if I have any sorts of questions/concerns related to riding in general or specifically for my bike, Adi is just a text message or call away -- he always responds very quickly. So to wrap up, I would recommend AK Motors to anyone who is looking to purchase a bike, without any reservations. <review>I bought my first motorcycle from Adi back in 2010, a Ninja 500R, and after referring several friends to him in the last five years, it finally came time for me to upgrade my own ride. When I saw he had gotten the exact bike I was searching for (an R6) in stock, I couldn't be happier. I accompanied my friends to a number of other dealerships, and no where else was I able to find salespeople who were as helpful, or inventories that provided as much selection.

While there's very little that hasn't passed through Adi's doors -- he's sold everything from jet skis to ATV's and Vespas -- Adi's specialization lies in beginner motorcycles. Adi takes the time to gauge your riding ability and make sure you end up with a bike that is well sized for your physical build (height and weight), and is powerful enough for you not to out-grow it right away, without being too heavy for you to learn on. He always has several options in varying price ranges, and never pushes you toward the more expensive bike. In order to ensure the best experience, he's happy to make any requested modifications to the bikes, like raising or lowering, or suggest aftermarket parts like raised handlebars to improve comfort and control.

Perhaps what I appreciate most, though, is Adi's patience and helpfulness. Even though he knew I was set on my R6, he was happy to let me test ride a number of other bikes first. When I got back, he was helping another customer, and was once again helpful and patient as ever, answering a number of questions about maintenance and aftermarket luggage options in case the customer wanted to take the bike touring.

In short, all my friends and I have found AK Motors to provide the absolute best of the two worlds of buying used bikes: you get the personal attention and great value typically found only in private sales, and the selection, professionalism, and registration services of an established dealership. Enjoy!</review>< resp>

< Text>
The best place to buy a bike. Awesome first time experience.  I went in with a good amount of questions. No one seemed annoyed or like they had anything better to do. One guy Thomas was working on a bike and stopped what he was doing to answer questions, pull bikes, talk about them. I rode off that day (friday) drove around a bit in the little side streets felt i was comfortable enough for riding home. Hands down the best place to buy a bike. Weather it be your first or not these guys know what they are talking about and are friendly with an extremely awesome mood towards making the customers happy.  Ill never go anywhere else.</Text>

< time>
1478645732845<//time>
<rating>5</rating>< Text>
If you work in downtown Santa Monica, free yourself from the ubiquitous Starbucks, and the idiosyncratic Philz-- and elect The Refinery.

This place has a crazy-friendly staff, and MOST IMPORTANTLY the coffee is transcendent. Delicious. Perfect. The lovingly crafted drinks cause customers to sigh audibly with satisfaction as they take their first sip. All the classic coffee concoctions have a place here -- as well as a few tasty teas.

With each visit, I reflect with pride on my decision to patronize such a fine establishment. The service is quick and efficient without sacrificing quality -- a rare balance to strike in the coffee shop game. You feel as if the composition of your drink was handled with care, but without the self-indulgent posturing you'll find at competitors.

If you're not in a rush to get back to the office, take a moment to enjoy the cool air inside, or warmth of the outdoor seating. The shop invites groups to stay and chat with their ample table seating, while offering bar stools for the staunch individualist seeking respite from the world outside.

If you are truly a discriminating coffee drinker, give these people your money.<//Text>

< review>
I absolutely love this shop. There are so many fresh flavors to choose from, all handcrafted and unique. There are different textures as well, from the smooth and icy Italian ices, to the creamy classic ice creams. In between them are the creme ices which are both creamy and have a nice icy texture. So delicious. I have not been disappointed in any of the flavors I have tried. They have real ingredients and don't taste artificial.
The shop's owner is always super friendly and knowledgeable. They also offer reward points for purchases. Please try this shop out, it truly is a gem. It's always nice to support small businesses like this!<//review>

<Review>It was my first time here. I always drive by this place on my way to Mt. Rubidoux and that day I decided to finally try this place.
First, I love the theme and atmosphere here. When you walk in you're instantly hit with the 1950s gas station/grease monkey theme. Lots of garage and car memorabilia on the walls and counters. Very clean too. I went on (Taco Tuesday) and thankfully came at the right time before it got too busy. Everyone working there was very patient, friendly and efficient. I got my food in 10 minutes after ordering which surprised me because it was a little busy. We were able to sit outside which had plenty of seating. It was a nice and chill day. The patio was nicely covered from the sun. The food was delicious and you get a lot for what you pay for. I will return in the future when I'm in the area.< /Review></record>

So glad I found this place, the food is great and the service is awesome too. Stopped by for a breakfast burrito and went back for a late lunch. It's right by my office in downtown Riverside and I come here often and it hasn't let me down so far. If you want good breakfast or lunch burritos stop by taco station, you won't regret it.</Text>

<userid>105566893250277268069< /userid><Name>Robert Lewis< /Name><time>1598668359247</time><rating>4</rating>< Review>
It was... okay? The highlight is the customer service. The staff really is super friendly. The food was borderline "meh" however. The burrito was not hot, but had good flavor, yet most certainly did not have enough protein in it. They also failed to serve my chips and guac with the plate, which I did not notice until I was nearly done with my burrito (was hungry! lol). They refunded the missing items without question. Lastly, the margarita Fresca was nice, not overly sweet, but on the small side; was half ice.

5 stars for service and 3 stars for food. Would not return.</Review>

< Review>
It was... okay? The highlight is the customer service. The staff really is super friendly. The food was borderline "meh" however. The burrito was not hot, but had good flavor, yet most certainly did not have enough protein in it. They also failed to serve my chips and guac with the plate, which I did not notice until I was nearly done with my burrito (was hungry! lol). They refunded the missing items without question. Lastly, the margarita Fresca was nice, not overly sweet, but on the small side; was half ice.

5 stars for service and 3 stars for food. Would not return.</Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Text>
Ok.  Looking for authentic Mexican Tacos but settled for here.  The second time in a Riverside Mexican place with no AC.  What is with the no AC in this area, I guess we are in Mexico.

Ok a bit over priced and a little too USA Mexican but we were hungry.

They have misters outside but still hot, but the beer is ice cold and a great selection  so who cares about the heat.

The food was good.  I think the corn tortillas for our Tacos were home made they were excellent.

So 5 stars for beer, food and sitting outside, 4 stars for price.<//Text>

< text>
Fantastic fish and shrimp tacos, as well as chorizo and Al pastor, in a place with great decor based on the fact it used to be a gas station. Wine, beer and Margaritas are available too. Copious outdoor seating that was there before Covid, so it doesn't feel like you're sitting in a parking lot. However, ordering is a bit like a fish tank inside, which plucked the Covid-anxiety strings. Located in quirkily SoCal downtown Riverside, which is well worth a visit in itself.</text>

We went to Taco Station after seeing the Christmas lights at the Mission Inn. The restaurant is less than a 10-minute walk from downtown.

Although it was a busy Saturday night, service was fast, and the food very good. I had the al pastor burrito and my wife, the fish taco. The salsa was delicious, especially the avocado salsa, which had just the right amount of heat.

Lastly, Taco Station serves beer and margaritas for those that want the full experience.< /text>

I loved the hedges that looked like old time automobiles.  And, the old gas pumps took me back to my childhood.
It is a very casual place with shaded outdoor eating.  I loved it!</review>

< Review>
I've been here a few times and the decor is definitely the star here.  It's cool to see all the old gas station stuff and I believe they name their combos creatively with car themed names.  The food itself isn't anything to write home about, there wasn't anything memorable other than the food seemed a bit overpriced.  It's a good place to stop by if you're in the area, but don't expect anything great.<//Review>

< review>
A well done Cali-Mission style Mexican food joint in the guise of a 1950's style full service  Gas Station. Seating inside and out with beer and alchohol available for purchase and a tone of license plates, car badges and other automotive memorabilia on the walls.  Great food as well, served quickly.</review>
